  "body": "### Description\nBesu is generating a lot of IO unnecessarily in normal operation\n\nAs a user, I want Besu to perform less IO in general so that it is more stable on slower disks, wears down disks less, and allows Besu to operate more quickly, if operating more from RAM. \nNeed to identify more areas where IO contention is commonplace \n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n* Less IO in general\n* More usage of caching and in-memory functions for Besu\n\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\n* Need caching in more areas - R/W caching\n* Doing less work, persisting less to the disk, persisting trie logs but not the worldstate (Amez / Karim) \n \n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\n* We are not using the flat DB during block processing, so have to gather a lot of data from disk \n* The first hotspot in Besu is reading data from RocksDB using the RocksDB.get method. This is mainly caused by the fact that we have to get most of the WorldState nodes from the Patricia Merkle Trie. All the details are in this document.",
